race.comment: BANNERED (3) led first-up at Pinjarra and was only claimed late, beaten 0.3L in a strong performance. His trial coming in was very impressive as well and drawing the inside today is a big tick. Can set the tempo again today and go one better. ROCK THE MARKET (7) is knocking on the door of her maiden win, bumping into one last start who jumped favourite on Saturday. She was only 0.8L away there, following a nose defeat first-up. Awkward gate, but she's third-up now and can shed the maiden tag. GODLESS STORM (2) was off a 561-day break coming into this campaign but has been solid since returning. He was just too far back at Belmont last time out and back up to 1200m today is a big tick. Winkers go one and a forward showing is likely. I'M ODETTE (13) keeps Pike in the saddle from her recent trials and can make an impression. COMMON TOUCH (4) hasn't been far away recently and has claims with the winkers on first time.
